FBIS4-36195 "drnes109_r_94002" FBIS-NES-94-109 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 India Talks With Russian Deputy Prime Minister Continue Talks With Russian Deputy Prime Minister Continue Nuclear Cooperation To Continue BK0606045194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 GMT 6 Jun 94 BK0606045194 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The deputy prime minister of Russia, Mr. Yuriy Yarov, says Indo-Russian cooperation in nuclear science will continue, particularly in the exchange of technology and scientists. He was speaking in Bombay yesterday after visiting the Bhaba Atomic Research Center. Mr. Yarov lauded India's nuclear science development. The Russian deputy prime minister also visited the Mazagaon dock. Mr. Yarov called for joint ventures between India and Russia in the ship-building area.
